  "prompt": "Why does my friend (girl) don't like other girls talking to me?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your female friend might feel uncomfortable with other girls talking to you:\n\n1. Jealousy\n- She may have romantic feelings for you\n- She might be possessive of your friendship\n- She could be insecure about your relationships with other girls\n\n2. Trust issues\n- She might worry about potential romantic competition\n- She could have past experiences that make her anxious\n- She may fear losing your friendship\n\n3. Personal insecurities\n- Low self-esteem\n- Fear of being replaced\n- Attachment concerns\n\n4. Friendship dynamics\n- She might see you as her primary friend\n- Protective of your friendship\n- Wants to maintain a close connection\n\n5. Misunderstandings\n- Cultural or personal background influences\n- Misinterpreted social interactions\n\nTo understand her true feelings, it's best to:\n- Communicate openly\n- Ask her directly about her concerns\n- Listen without being defensive\n- Reassure her about your friendship\n\nRemember, healthy friendships are built on trust, respect, and open communication.",
